explanation: The solution uses a lexicographical generation approach. It maintains a vector representing the current combination and iteratively generates the next combination by incrementing the rightmost character and adjusting subsequent characters. This approach ensures efficient generation of all combinations in lexicographical order. The time complexity is O(N) as each character is processed at most once. The space complexity is O(K) due to the storage of the current combination. Energy implications are low as the algorithm involves minimal memory access and computation.

